                            <__p_name>insert_from_xml</__p_name>
                            <__p_description>Inserts blocks into this model at the given parent index and row loaded from the given XML.</__p_description>
                            <__p_return_description>Total number of blocks that were inserted into this model.</__p_return_description>
                            <__p_inlines>Get the parent block of the given parent index, making sure it worked and the given row is valid.

Create a new qt XML reader stream attached to the given XML byte array.

Read the next start element and make sure it is the copy tag.

Read the next start element, making sure it is the language tag and the language is the same as this model's currently loaded project's language.

Initialize an empty list of loaded blocks and continue reading the XML stream until the end.

Get the next XML node and check to see if it is a start element.

Load the block from its XML tag.

If the given parent block can have the loaded block as a child then append it to the loaded block list.

Push a new insert command to this model's undo stack using the loaded block list and then return the number of blocks inserted.
</__p_inlines>
