                            <__p_description>Inserts the given blocks into the given parent index at the given row. The given parent index and row must be valid.</__p_description>
                            <__p_inlines>Get the parent block of the given parent index, making sure it works and the given row is valid.

Initialize the volatile above indicator and signal this model is inserting new rows.

Insert the entire list of given blocks into the parent block starting at the given row, setting the volatile above indicator to true if any one of the inserted blocks are volatile above.

Finish the row insertion.

If any of the blocks were volatile above then push updates accordingly.

Signal this model has been modified.
