                        <__p_type>Public</__p_type>
                        <Function>
                            <__p_name>highlightBlock</__p_name>
                            <__p_description>Implements the qtg.QSyntaxHighlighter interface.</__p_description>
                            <__p_inlines>Initialize the search start and regular expression.

Continue while there are still words to check.

Attempt to get the next word matched, breaking out if there are no more words left.

Check the words spelling, settings its format as misspelled if it is as such.

Update the search start to the end of the last word matched.
</__p_inlines>
                            <__p_static>0</__p_static>
                            <__p_abstract>0</__p_abstract>
                            <Object>
                                <__p_name>text</__p_name>
                                <__p_description>See qt docs.</__p_description>
                            </Object>
                        </Function>
                    </Access>
                </Class>
                <Class>
                    <__p_name>Spell_Checker</__p_name>
                    <__p_description>This is the spell checker class. It inherits the qt group box widget. It provides a spell checking and correction interface. It uses the Hunspell library for all speller functions.

It provides a spell checking and correction interface. It begins spell checking with its start slot, providing it a qt text cursor that is uses to parse the entire document of the text cursor, checking for misspelled words. Each misspelled word is highlighted and waits on the user to correct. The user is given options to use a suggestion, replace, ignore, stop, or add to dictionary. The cursor is updated to highlight each misspelled word found while waiting for the user to make a choice about it. Adding to dictionary is currently defunct but will be fixed.
</__p_description>
                    <__p_parents>qtw.QGroupBox</__p_parents>
                    <Access>
                        <__p_name>Initialize</__p_name>
                        <__p_type>Public</__p_type>
                        <Function>
                            <__p_name>__init__</__p_name>
                            <__p_description>Initializes a new speller checker with the given title, dictionary, and optional parent.</__p_description>
                            <__p_inlines>Initialize the Hunspell object with the given dictionary, appending the root path and appropriate extensions.

Initialize the word label and edit widgets used for each misspelled word found.

Initialize the cursor to none and list of suggested words to an empty list.

Setup this new widget's GUI.
</__p_inlines>
                            <__p_static>0</__p_static>
                            <__p_abstract>0</__p_abstract>
                            <Object>
                                <__p_name>title</__p_name>
                                <__p_description>The title of this new spell checker's qt group box.</__p_description>
                            </Object>
                            <Object>
                                <__p_name>dictionary</__p_name>
                                <__p_description>The Hunspell dictionary used for spell checking. This does not include the directory or file extensions, for example &quot;en_US&quot;.</__p_description>
                            </Object>
                            <Object>
                                <__p_name>parent</__p_name>
                                <__p_description>An optional qt object parent for this new spell checker.</__p_description>
                                <__p_assignment>None</__p_assignment>
                            </Object>
                        </Function>
                    </Access>
                    <Access>
                        <__p_name>Signals</__p_name>
                        <__p_type>Public</__p_type>
                        <Object>
                            <__p_name>finished</__p_name>
                            <__p_description>Signals this spell checker has finished checking and correcting for misspelled words.</__p_description>
                            <__p_assignment>qtc.Signal()</__p_assignment>
                        </Object>
                        <Object>
                            <__p_name>cursor_changed</__p_name>
                            <__p_description>Signals this spell checker has changed the cursor given to it.</__p_description>
                            <__p_assignment>qtc.Signal(qtg.QTextCursor)</__p_assignment>
                        </Object>
                    </Access>
                    <Access>
                        <__p_name>Slots</__p_name>
                        <__p_type>Public</__p_type>
                        <Function>
                            <__p_name>start</__p_name>
                            <__p_description>Called to have this spell checker begin checking for misspelled words in the document of the given qt text cursor. The entire document is checked for misspelled words. If this spell checker is already checking a document then this does nothing.</__p_description>
                            <__p_inlines>Make sure this spell checker is not currently checking a document.

Set this spell checker's cursor to the one given and move it to the beginning of the document.

Find the next misspelled word.
</__p_inlines>
                            <__p_descriptors>qtc.Slot(qtg.QTextCursor)</__p_descriptors>
                            <__p_static>0</__p_static>
                            <__p_abstract>0</__p_abstract>
                            <Object>
                                <__p_name>cursor</__p_name>
                                <__p_description>A qt text cursor whose document is checked for misspelled words.</__p_description>
                            </Object>
                        </Function>
                    </Access>
                    <Access>
                        <__p_name>Methods</__p_name>
                        <__p_type>Private</__p_type>
                        <Function>
                            <__p_name>__find_next_word_</__p_name>
                            <__p_description>Finds the next misspelled word in the current document this spell checker is checking. If no misspelled word is found once the end of the document is reached then it stops this spell checker.</__p_description>
                            <__p_inlines>Get this spell checker's cursor and compile the regular expression for matching words.

Continue until a misspelled word is found or the cursor reaches the end of the document.

Select the word under the cursor and make sure it is a word.

Get the speller and selected word.

If the word is misspelled then signal the cursor has changed, update the word label and edit widgets with the misspelled word, and update the list of suggestions for the new misspelled word.

Move to the next word in the cursor's document, stopping this spell checker if the end of the document is reached.
</__p_inlines>
                            <__p_static>0</__p_static>
                            <__p_abstract>0</__p_abstract>
                        </Function>
