                        <Function>
                            <__p_name>__add_</__p_name>
                            <__p_description>Called to add the currently selected misspelled word to the run time dictionary. This is currently defunct so TO BE DONE.</__p_description>
                            <__p_static>0</__p_static>
                            <__p_abstract>0</__p_abstract>
                            <__p_descriptors>qtc.Slot()</__p_descriptors>
                        </Function>
                        <Function>
                            <__p_name>__suggest_</__p_name>
                            <__p_description>Called to offer a suggested word in this spell checker's word edit widget. This finds the next word in the list of suggestions. If this spell checker is not actively checking a document then this does nothing.</__p_description>
                            <__p_static>0</__p_static>
                            <__p_abstract>0</__p_abstract>
                            <__p_inlines>Make sure this spell checker is active.

Find the index to the next word in this spell checker's list of suggestions, wrapping to the beginning if its word edit widget is on the last word or an unknown word.

Update the word edit widget with the next suggested word.
</__p_inlines>
                            <__p_descriptors>qtc.Slot()</__p_descriptors>
                        </Function>
                        <Function>
                            <__p_name>__replace_</__p_name>
                            <__p_description>Called to replace the selected misspelled word with the text of this spell checker's word edit widget. This then moves the cursor forward looking for the next misspelled word. If this spell checker is not actively checking a document then this does nothing.</__p_description>
                            <__p_static>0</__p_static>
                            <__p_abstract>0</__p_abstract>
                            <__p_inlines>Make sure this spell checker is active.

Replace the cursor's selected word with this spell checker's word edit value.

Move the cursor to the next word, continuing or finishing if there is a word or not, respectively.
</__p_inlines>
                            <__p_descriptors>qtc.Slot()</__p_descriptors>
                        </Function>
                        <Function>
                            <__p_name>__ignore_</__p_name>
                            <__p_description>Called to ignore the selected misspelled word, simply skipping it and moving the cursor forward looking for the next misspelled word. If this spell checker is not actively checking a document then this does nothing.</__p_description>
                            <__p_static>0</__p_static>
                            <__p_abstract>0</__p_abstract>
                            <__p_inlines>Make sure this spell checker is active.

Move the cursor to the next word, continuing or finishing if there is a word or not, respectively.
</__p_inlines>
                            <__p_descriptors>qtc.Slot()</__p_descriptors>
                        </Function>
                        <Function>
                            <__p_name>__stop_</__p_name>
                            <__p_description>Called to stop this spell checker, finishing its spell checking of the current document. If this spell checker is not actively checking a document then this does nothing.</__p_description>
                            <__p_static>0</__p_static>
                            <__p_abstract>0</__p_abstract>
                            <__p_inlines>Make sure this spell checker is active.

Reset this spell checker's cursor to none and its list of suggested words to empty.

Signal that this spell checker has finished.
</__p_inlines>
