                    </Access>
                    <Access>
                        <__p_name>Methods</__p_name>
                        <__p_type>Private</__p_type>
                        <Function>
                            <__p_name>__build_form_widget_</__p_name>
                            <__p_description>Builds and initializes all edit widgets for all properties of the block at the given index based off its edit definitions, adding them to this dock's list of edit widgets. This clears any previous edit widgets from the last index that was built by this method.</__p_description>
                            <__p_return_description>The form layout containing all built edit widgets and the apply button at the end.</__p_return_description>
                            <__p_static>0</__p_static>
                            <__p_abstract>0</__p_abstract>
                            <__p_inlines>Clear any existing edit widgets of this dock.

Get the properties and edit definitions of the block at the given index.

Initialize the qt form layout.

Iterate through all edit definitions.

Initialize the edit widget, label, and hidden names.

If this is a line edit definition then initialize its edit widget and label.

Else if this is a text edit definition then initialize its edit widget and label.

Else if this is a check box edit definition then initialize its edit widget and leave the label blank.

Else if this is a combo box edit definition then initialize its edit widget and label.

Else if this is a hidden edit definition then initialize its dummy edit widget and set it as hidden.

Else this is an invalid edit definition so throw an exception.

If the new edit widget is not hidden then add it to the form layout.

Append the edit widget to this dock's list.

Add a new apply button to the end of the form layout.

Initialize a new widget, setting its layout to the form layout.

Return the new widget.

If any exception occurs during the build process then clear this dock's list of edit widgets and raise it again.
</__p_inlines>
                            <Object>
                                <__p_name>index</__p_name>
                                <__p_description>The index of the block whose property edit widgets are built.</__p_description>
                            </Object>
                        </Function>
                        <Function>
                            <__p_name>__build_apply_</__p_name>
                            <__p_description>Builder method.</__p_description>
                            <__p_return_description>A qt layout containing a new apply button initialized to work this this dock' slot.</__p_return_description>
                            <__p_static>0</__p_static>
                            <__p_abstract>0</__p_abstract>
                            <__p_inlines>Initialize a new apply button for this dock.

Initialize a qt horizontal box layout. Add the new apply button and the and then a stretch.

Return the box layout.
</__p_inlines>
                        </Function>
                    </Access>
                    <Access>
                        <__p_name>Slots</__p_name>
                        <__p_type>Private</__p_type>
                        <Function>
                            <__p_name>__current_changed_</__p_name>
                            <__p_description>Called to update the block this dock is editing to the new one at the given index. if the given index is invalid then this dock returns to a null state with no form.</__p_description>
                            <__p_static>0</__p_static>
                            <__p_abstract>0</__p_abstract>
                            <__p_inlines>If the given index is valid then update this dock's window title and build a new form of edit widgets based off the given index.

Else the given index is invalid so clear this dock's window title and edit widgets.
</__p_inlines>
                            <__p_descriptors>qtc.Slot(qtc.QModelIndex)</__p_descriptors>
                            <Object>
                                <__p_name>index</__p_name>
                                <__p_description>The index of the new block whose properties are edited by this dock.</__p_description>
                            </Object>
                        </Function>
                        <Function>
                            <__p_name>__apply_</__p_name>
                            <__p_description>Called to set this dock's view's currently indexed block's properties to the current values of its edit widgets. If the current index is not valid then this does nothing.</__p_description>
                            <__p_static>0</__p_static>
                            <__p_abstract>0</__p_abstract>
                            <__p_inlines>Get this dock's view's current index and make sure it is valid.

Set the properties of the current index to the values of this dock's edit widgets.
</__p_inlines>
                            <__p_descriptors>qtc.Slot()</__p_descriptors>
                        </Function>
                    </Access>
                </Class>
